messages.message:
Hey, I've seen some slightly weird behaviour here (https://aihub.instabase.com/build/01955c89-689c-7bfa-ab8d-95d189ca5768) that happen with validations that used to work (probably due to the recent model upgrades). In this example, the extraction shown in the UI is 'ASOS.COM (http://ASOS.COM) LIMITED' which is correct. However, when trying to validate this result, I found that there is actually 3 whitespaces between the two words in the result. I could not tell this from either the print logs or the UI extracted results view as they seem to shrink the whitespace down to 1.

I had to include some extra code to account for this case when validating which was not ideal but not a big lift. It was more the debugging that took quite some time. `response_dict['company_name'] != ' '.join(Company_Name.split())`
seems that discussion for this has moved to https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1741280109256749?thread_ts=1741259632.895719&cid=C05BJCNKZAM
